# EsperantAI — Cursor Rules

## Project
EsperantAI — AI gesture controller for streamers. Vanilla JS web app, no bundler, no React.

## Code Style
- Window globals (no ES modules): `window.ClassName`
- IIFE pattern: `(async function() { ... })().catch()`
- `'use strict'` at top of every file
- All visible text goes through i18n: `data-i18n="key.path"` in HTML, `window.i18n.t('key')` in JS
- `en-US.json` is the source of truth for translations

## Architecture
- `core/` — Main logic (detector, trigger-engine, action-engine, config, i18n, license, history)
- `adapters/` — Streaming software (OBS, Streamlabs, vMix, XSplit) — extend `AdapterBase`
- `platforms/` — Stream platforms (Twitch, YouTube, Kick, Trovo, StreamElements) — extend `PlatformBase`
- `locales/` — 13 translation JSON files

## Critical Rules
1. Always use `_escape()` for dynamic HTML content (XSS prevention)
2. `config.set()` is debounced — use `config.flush()` for immediate writes
3. License tier gating: `window.licenseManager.hasFeature('featureName')` before showing/enabling features
4. Never bypass TIER_FEATURES — check tier before exposing Pro/Pro+ features
5. OAuth tokens should use sessionStorage, not localStorage
6. Test any trigger-engine changes against both continuous AND punctual triggers
7. Preserve backward compatibility: `getActionsForTrigger()` auto-converts legacy `scenes.{trigger}` to multi-action format

## i18n
- Add new keys to `locales/en-US.json` FIRST
- Then update all 12 other locale files
- Template variables: `{message}`, `{attempt}`, `{max}`, `{count}`, etc.
- RTL support: ar-SA has `_meta.rtl: true`

## Key Methods
- `config.get('path.to.key', fallback)` — dot-notation config access
- `config.set('path', value)` — debounced save
- `config.flush()` — immediate save
- `triggerEngine.process(result)` — main detection loop entry
- `actionEngine.execute(actions)` — parallel action execution
- `window.triggerHistory.add(entry)` — log trigger event
